Expanding Capacity of a ∩ Deployment on &gke;
If the current capacity of your ∩ deployment is insufficient for your workloads, you can expand the capacity using the procedure in this section.
These instructions assume you have followed the procedure in and have a running ∩ deployment on &aks;. The instructions below will use environment variables defined in .
Get the most recently created node in the cluster.
&prompt.user;RECENT_VM_NODE=$(gcloud compute instances list --filter=name~${CLUSTER_NAME:?required} --format json | jq --raw-output '[sort_by(.creationTimestamp) | .[].creationTimestamp ] | last | .[0:19] | strptime("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S") | mktime')
Increase the &kube; node count in the cluster. Replace the example value with the number of nodes required for your workload.
&prompt.user;gcloud container clusters resize $CLUSTER_NAME \ --num-nodes 5
Verify the new nodes are in a Ready state before proceeding.
&prompt.user;kubectl get nodes
Add or update the following in your &values-filename; file to increase the number of diego-cell in your ∩ deployment. Replace the example value with the number required by your workflow.
sizing: diego_cell: instances: 5
Perform a helm upgrade to apply the change.
&prompt.user;helm upgrade kubecf suse/kubecf \ --namespace kubecf \ --values &values-file; \ --version &kubecf_chart;
Monitor progress of the additional diego-cell pods:
&prompt.user;watch --color 'kubectl get pods --namespace kubecf'
